<br>
From my knowledge, the rain spells are described so: THREE waves of rain that can hit FOUR mobs at most.<br>
<br>
What I saw however was TWO waves only when I used it on several mobs (two mobs was the most I used it on, didnt want to risk to create too much aggro).<br>
<br>
Can anyone explain the working of those spells in greater detail? Why are there only two waves if there is more than one mob?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarmatyr1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#333333>(8/9/02 7:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rain spells...what you always wanted to know</span><hr size=1> Umm...not too hard.<br>
<br>
Max of three waves. Max of four hits. If you have four mobs, they will all be hit once. If you have three mobs, you'll hit three the first wave, and one the second wave, and there will be no third wave. if you have two mobs, you'll hit both on two waves. If you have one mob, you'll hit it with three waves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(8/9/02 2:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ahh</span><hr size=1> Your description is quite exactly what I observed. Now I'm just wondering...is this how rains were intended to work?<br>
<br>
If you consider them against targeted AE's, they are limited already (several waves on potentially moving target(s), several waves=more chances for resists, ...). And now not even the same (full) damage for all mobs hit by a rain!<br>
<br>
It seems that rains need a serious upgrade (or repair?). I realize that they do a lot more damage than targeted AE's but still...in the current version their use is so limited already.<br>
<br>
Three waves, hitting at most four mobs like targeted AE's...would that make rains too powerful (considering how much they are resisted)?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#333333>(8/9/02 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Waves...</span><hr size=1> Even if it hit four mobs first wave it still cast the other waves, even if it don't do any dmg.<br>
So....  Don't step into the AE area after wave one, you still will be hitted by it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kavinmagius>Kavin Magius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(8/9/02 2:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waves...</span><hr size=1> Someone had said a long time ago that rains initaly hit all targets in area 3 times but it was nerfed in beta because it was overpowering. I wonder with all the upgrades to mobs if it would now be too powerful.<br>
<br>
Kavin Magius<br>
54 Elementalist<br>
Antonius Bayle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(8/10/02 9:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waves...</span><hr size=1> Heh, if it actually did hit all mobs in the area for 3 waves you would have one very dead Mage .5 seconds into the 2nd wave. <p><CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157442">Xasha Maelstrom</A> (Prev: Usrbinperl Dashw)<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=290740">Gothique Darkmagik</A><BR>
<IMG SRC="http://home.columbus.rr.com/keeferfam/images/kill-maestro.gif">
</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 3:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/neriakwraith.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waves...</span><hr size=1> Well, I've been using rains alot with my mage lately, and I've noticed some other weird stuff. From parsing my logs, resists on the waves seem to get higher the more waves you get. These are the numbers I'm getting:<br>
<br>
1st wave: ~25% chance of resist<br>
2nd wave: ~25% chance to resist<br>
3rd wave: ~50% chance to resist<br>
<br>
In other words, you're less likely to resist the more mobs you're hitting, but you get less damage output that way.<br>
<br>
I think the spells were coded this way to sort of reduce them being used for single targets (which I use them for alot). It makes sense, because on single targets, they eventually become quite mana efficient. <p><CENTER>
<EMBED src="http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/barcode.swf" quality=high bgcolor=#000000  WIDTH="220" HEIGHT="60" NAME="barcode" ALIGN="" TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer"></EMBED></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarmatyr1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 9:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Waves...</span><hr size=1> At 39, rain of lava (or whatever) is crap for a single target. Even for multiple targets, I don't think it hits the mana ratio of the bolt with bracer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 8:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yep</span><hr size=1> Hehe yes thats why I'm unsure at lvl 55 how rain spells work <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  never really used them (except to cast once for a test).<br>
<br>
Sirocco however is quite different, it is an efficient and nice spell against single targets. I have tried it out on some single and multiple targets and found it to be a useful spell, compared to the pre-50 rain spells. The latter have really been &quot;nerfed&quot; by the introduction of the damage focus item(s), since with that you can get almost the same damage much more reliable.<br>
<br>
Maybe rain spells should be looked at. I love Sirocco, but I can understand any pre-50 mage who refuses to use their rains (as did I)...they're just too unreliable and inefficient.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uazixdamage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azix Da Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(8/14/02 10:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.oek.dk/~vip/image/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yep</span><hr size=1> yeah I would love a rain spell with 3 waves but no limit on number of mobs, would make AE groups a little easie, and then I could regen a lot of mana from those frog casters in OS. <p><table width="100%" border="0"><tr width="25%"><td rowspan="2" width="25%" align="center"></td><td width="50%" align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22508" target="new">Azix LFG</a></td><td rowspan="2" width="25%" align="center"></td></tr><tr><td height="160" align="center"><a href="http://www.nexxus.dk" target="new"><img src="http://www.oek.dk/~vip/image/sig.gif" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxurtsdunnit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xurts Dunnit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(8/14/02 5:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yep</span><hr size=1> Regen mana from a caster mob?<br>
<br>
Please explain.  Manastorm is not a theft of mana.. it is a drain of mana.  What are you doing to regen mana from a caster frog? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=11yadin11>11yadin11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 2:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1467.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yep</span><hr size=1>  Only larg mobs get hit 3 times.. giants, wurms ect. Everything else gets hit 2 times tops and if you have a pet in the mix it can chew up a wave on the larger mobs. I'm one of the few mages that SWEARS by his rain spells, if the situation is correct they can kick all kinds. My personal best situation would be a raid with single pulls of mobs that live long enough to be debuffed. Sure you miss a fair bit but even when you 2 outa 3 waves its worth it in my book. By the way.. nothing like doin almost 2k dmg(manastorm) for some good ol raid exp =)<br>
