<br>
Take 3 rains for example.. Scirocco, Manastorm, Maelstrom of Electricity.  If you debuff your mob first.. you have better success... and yes this can get you in trouble if soloing.. but an Epic pet does a remarkable job of keeping agro off you.  I still prefer to do this in groups.<br>
 Cast your first rain.. as soon as your gems pop cast your second rain.. (your first rain will still be refreshing its gem when you can cast your second rain), then as soon as your gems refresh cast your third rain.  The third wave of the first rain and the first wave of the second rain will overlap (ie hit at the same time), same with the second and third.. third and forth etc etc... (sustained damage).<br>
<br>
You can deal out some insane damage this way in an incredibly short amount of time.  I was in CT yesterday doing this.. and could land 18 waves or rain in one fight with 2 or 3 resists per mob.  I was only doing it for fun, but you're doing about 10k (get some crits.. 13k), damage in a minute and a half or so, plus whatever your pet is doing.  I double stack rains in FG all the time.. shrooms live about 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
