<br>
BTW, mobs cannot &quot;resist&quot; the damage application from a DoT that has landed.  Once the DoT lands, it does it's max damage every tic for the rest of the duration of the spell.  DoTs work like Snares (i.e. fixed duration and effect) not like Roots (i.e. a saving throw every tic).<br>
